annotationA: Vinculin; Involved in cell adhesion. May be involved in the attachment of the actin-based microfilaments to the plasma membrane; Belongs to the vinculin/alpha-catenin family
annotationB: Parvin, isoform A; Parvin is a Calponin-homology protein that together with Ilk and stck reinforces integrin-matrix adhesion at muscle attachment sites in the developing embryo. Parvin roles include cell adhesion and actin cytoskeleton organisation in muscles, wing and eye epithelial cells
